                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14730657" author="lian cheng" created="Fri, 4 Sep 2015 11:09:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The reason is that all non-empty strings are converted to &lt;tt&gt;true&lt;/tt&gt; when casting to boolean. This behavior isn&apos;t intuitive, but it is consistent with Hive. I&apos;m not sure whether we want to change this. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;PostgreSQL only allows string literals &lt;tt&gt;&apos;true&apos;&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;&apos;false&apos;&lt;/tt&gt; to be casted to boolean (case insensitive), casting any other strings to boolean results in error.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14735668" author="yhuai" created="Tue, 8 Sep 2015 21:39:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=lian+cheng&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;lian cheng&quot;&gt;lian cheng&lt;/a&gt; Looks like postgresql support more string literals (see &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.postgresql.org/docs/devel/static/datatype-boolean.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.postgresql.org/docs/devel/static/datatype-boolean.html&lt;/a&gt;), e.g. &lt;tt&gt;yes&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;no&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14735682" author="yhuai" created="Tue, 8 Sep 2015 21:46:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A related Hive jira is &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-3604&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-3604&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14738655" author="apachespark" created="Thu, 10 Sep 2015 12:22:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;cloud-fan&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/8698&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/8698&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14741546" author="yhuai" created="Fri, 11 Sep 2015 21:15:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Issue resolved by pull request 8698&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/8698&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/8698&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14741550" author="yhuai" created="Fri, 11 Sep 2015 21:17:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We need to document this behavior change in our release note. The new behavior is that casting a string to a boolean will return true for &apos;t&apos; &apos;true&apos; &apos;y&apos; &apos;yes&apos; &apos;1&apos;,  false for &apos;f&apos; &apos;false&apos; &apos;n&apos; &apos;no&apos; &apos;0&apos; and null for others. The matching of those literals are case in-sensitive.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
